# S05-T05: Long-Press Actions

## Objective
Long-press on map/video surfaces opens a contextual radial menu (e.g., set waypoint, mark target, ping).

## Acceptance Criteria
- Long-press (500ms) on video opens radial menu at touch point.
- Menu items: Mark Target, Set Waypoint, Ping, Cancel (4-item radial).
- 200ms scale-in (NOT spring) + opacity.
- Auto-dismiss on outside tap.

## Steps
1. Subscribe to gesture engine `longPress`.
2. Build `<RadialMenu>` component (4 buttons at 90° intervals).
3. Apply UI_REGULATION colors (cyan default, pink for Mark Target).
4. Dispatch selected action through Event Bus (S04-T05).

## Invariants
- No spring/bounce on open (UI_REGULATION).
- Menu items minimum 56×56px touch targets.
- Single menu instance at a time; new long-press replaces it.
